	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=31284"><span id="Scholar">xsikal</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">97 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.16]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Proccing a damage shield is no different than proccing a self-buff (like the Screaming Mace does) -- while in combat using this staff, there is a chance based off of your dex that it will proc, casting a damage shield on you.&nbsp;&nbsp;The two-handed practice sword, in play since Kunark, has a similar effect.<br/><br/>That said, this effect doesn't seem so useful, given that the staff is wieldable only by casters -- if a caster is both (a) in battle and swinging this staff instead of casting/medding and (b) the target of the mob's aggression instead of the group tanks, then something is going seriously wrong.<br/><br/>That said, the stats/mana/saves are pretty nice. :)  I'm just not sure the proc is anything but a point of curiosity.<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
